name: Next Day Xmas Delivery

name: ChristmasMania Tee
description:

Fire up the Roman Reindeer cos it's beginning to smell a lot like Christmas!!! For us in Parts Unknown, Christmas is the second biggest holiday of the year (behind the 'Day of the Warrior'!) and we decided it's high time we made it a lot more wrestle-y. So we put together a Christmas design that incorporates all that we love about the season, from Barb Wire tinsel to the MitB Christmas tree ladder, and turned into a faux knit pattern for the truly bad Christmas jumper look. A winner is you at the Christmas Party this year, cos after all Santa is still real to us DAMMIT! Of course, not everyone likes a jumper, so we thought a t-shirt would be just as cool. Printed on Gildan Premium Forest Green or Gildan Softstyle Cardinal Red shirts. Design is white screen print NOT KNITTED! This design is also available as an equally awesome Christmas Jumper! name: One Giant Leap
description:
In Stock! Shipping now.

June 28, 1998 a human body is thrown 16 feet from the roof of a cage through the Spanish announce table. It was truly one small step, but one giant leap for mankind as this moment was replayed all over the world. A stunt like this had never been seen by such a mainstream audience and it was the talk of the wrestling world for months and is still talked about as a key moment of the era. Our design features an illustration of a cage with the slogan "ONE GIANT LEAP FOR MANKIND" and the 16 feet measurement. The reverse features the slogan "Putting Some Butts in the Seats: Since 1986". This is for true fans, hardcore wrestling's finest hour, in t-shirt form. Product images for Illustration only, product may differ slightly due to printing techniques. Print size is consistent throughout all sizes. Printed on Black Gildan Premium Ringspun (4100) shirts.

name: Foreign Objects
description:
In Stock! Shipping now.

UPDATED! Now features new title belt!
(Hey, it's better than the spinner!)

It's hard to believe in a sport with such fine refereeing that cheating occasionally happens, but it does. Over the years there has been many forms of cheating but by far the most interesting is the use of a 'Foreign Object'. For years we thought a Foreign Object was something that came from another country but that theory was thrown in to jeopardy when Duggan's American made 2x4 was described as 'foreign' by Gorilla. This forced a rethink and we eventually realised that it simply meant any object that was not part of the ring itself & was introduced from the outside. There have been so many awesome Foreign Objects we decided to chronicle them on a t-shirt (cos that's what we do!), this collection is by no means exhaustive but we think most of the classics are there from the Title Belts to Barb Wire, Baseball bats to Guitars, a Megaphone to Pillman's pistol and of course, the ultimate Foreign Object, the good old-fashioned Steel Chair! Product images for Illustration only, product may differ slightly due to printing techniques. Print size is consistent throughout all sizes. Printed on Black Gildan Premium Ringspun (4100) shirts.
